{
  "texts": [
    "Also, NNLFs have this property:L nn ∈ [0, 1].",
    "Accordingly, we can create NNLFs from active loss functions as follows.The Normalized Negative Cross Entropy (NNCE) is:L NNCE (f (x), y) = 1 - A + log p(y|x) K k=1 A + log p(k|x);(8)the Normalized Negative Focal Loss (NNFL) is:L NNFL (f (x), y) = 1 - A + (1 -p(y|x)) γ log p(y|x) K k=1 A + (1 -p(k|x)) γ log p(k|x).",
    "(9)As a closing remark, we note compared to the intermediate form, the unnormalized NLFs, the loss functions proposed above avoid the access to the ground-truth probability q.2) ANL Framework: We can now create new robust loss functions by replacing the MAE in APL with our proposed NNLF.",
    "Given an active loss function L, we propose Active Negative Loss (ANL) functions as follows:L ANL = αL norm + βL nn.",
    "(10)Here, α, β > 0 are parameters, L norm denotes the normalized L and L nn denotes the Normalized Negative Loss Function corresponding to L. Accordingly, we can create ANL from the two mentioned active loss functions as follows.For Cross Entropy (CE), we have ANL-CE:L ANL-CE = αL NCE + βL NNCE."
  ]
}